* Data Validation: Shows runners with missing critical fields.
*   When to use:    Before race day or after participant import to verify data quality.
*   How to use:     Double-click to display runners with missing data in the Browse window.
*   Customize:      Comment out (*) any field checks you don't need, or uncomment additional ones.
Destination         Browse

* Check for blank fields - add or remove checks as needed
Select              BIB
EQ
OR
Select              AGE
EQ
Or
Select              SEX
EQ
Or
Select              DIV
EQ
Or
Select              CHIP
EQ
Or
Select              RACE
EQ
Or
Select              FIRST NAME
EQ
Or
Select              LAST NAME
EQ
And
Select              BIB
NE                  0
* Uncomment additional checks as needed:
* Or
* Select              CITY
* EQ
* Or
* Select              STATE
* EQ

* The Field commands below are not used when Destination is Browse.
* Uncomment them if you change Destination to a text file (they define the output columns).
* Field               BIB
* Field               Name
* Field               Sex
* Field               AGE
* Field               DIV
* Field               CHIP
* Field               RACE
* Field               City
* Field               State